cial_op_track_log_unique_code.name: cial_op_track_log_unique_code
cial_op_track_log_unique_code.comment: Commercial operation tracking log unique ID. Concatenation of country ID, data source ID, and commercial operation tracking log ID with an underscore separator.

cial_op_tracking_log_event_date.name: cial_op_tracking_log_event_date
cial_op_tracking_log_event_date.comment: Tracking log date of last event

cial_op_tracking_log_url_type_code.name: cial_op_tracking_log_url_type_code
cial_op_tracking_log_url_type_code.comment: Internal tracking log URL type ID

cial_op_tracking_log_url_category_code.name: cial_op_tracking_log_url_category_code
cial_op_tracking_log_url_category_code.comment: Internal tracking log URL category ID. In Marketing Cloud, this is map to a html attribute called Alias or LinkName

cial_op_tracking_log_source_url.name: cial_op_tracking_log_source_url
cial_op_tracking_log_source_url.comment: Internal tracking log source URL. This field conaitns the URL in case of an email click. Ex : https://www.jumbo.pt/Frontoffice/mercearia_doce/selecao_natal?utm_source=newsletter&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=NestleChoco_2911

digital_src_type_code.name: digital_src_type_code
digital_src_type_code.comment: Digital source type ID. Physical device (ie : phone, table, PC)

digital_src_type_sde.name: digital_src_type_sde
digital_src_type_sde.comment: Digital source type description. Physical device (ie : phone, table, PC)

digital_src_subtype_code.name: digital_src_subtype_code
digital_src_subtype_code.comment: Digital source subtype ID. Physical device (ie : specific model of phone, tablet)

digital_src_subtype_sde.name: digital_src_subtype_sde
digital_src_subtype_sde.comment: Digital source subtype description. Physical device (ie : specific model of phone, tablet)

digital_channel_used.name: digital_channel_used
digital_channel_used.comment: Digital channel used. Browser used, application used...

data_src_code.name: data_src_code
data_src_code.comment: ID of the information system where the data is flowing from. Ex : MDM, EXTENDA, METI, DWH...

cre_date.name: cre_date
cre_date.comment: Date of creation of the data in the Datapool

upd_date.name: upd_date
upd_date.comment: Date of update of the data in the Datapool

ctry_code.name: ctry_code
ctry_code.comment: Refers to country ID (ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 norm) where the data coming from the information system is flowing from.

web_account_unique_code.name: web_account_unique_code
web_account_unique_code.comment: Unique web account ID. Concatenation of country ID, data source ID, web account id and web account start date.

cial_op_diff_log_unique_code.name: cial_op_diff_log_unique_code
cial_op_diff_log_unique_code.comment: Commercial operation diffusion log unique ID. Concatenation of person unique ID, and commercial operation diffusion log ID with an underscore separator.

digital_visit_unique_code.name: digital_visit_unique_code
digital_visit_unique_code.comment: Unique digital visit ID. Concatenation of country ID, data source ID, web account unique ID, and digital source ID.

cmp_id.name: cmp_id
cmp_id.comment: Primary key Technical Id of the campaign.

msg_channel.name: msg_channel
msg_channel.comment: Primary key Channel of the associated message

msg_frequency.name: msg_frequency
msg_frequency.comment: Frequency of the message. Contains the Corp Label.

msg_code.name: msg_code
msg_code.comment: Code of the campaign that will be automatically generated. The code will contain: - The country code (ISO 3) - MSG (static) - An increment of 6 digits

msg_update_date.name: msg_update_date
msg_update_date.comment: Last update date automatically generated (technical field) Not to be displayed and in UTC.

msg_creation_date.name: msg_creation_date
msg_creation_date.comment: Creation date automatically generated (technical field) Not to be displayed and in UTC.

msg_asset_id.name: msg_asset_id
msg_asset_id.comment: This is the technical Id of the campaign object inside SFMC. This field will be used in order to break the link between the message and the campaign in the deletion process

msg_perso_level.name: msg_perso_level
msg_perso_level.comment: Level of personalisation. Contains the Corp Label

msg_customer_activity.name: msg_customer_activity
msg_customer_activity.comment: Do I send messages to Active customers, Inactive ones or both. Contains the Corp Label

msg_drive_to.name: msg_drive_to
msg_drive_to.comment: Who is the sender of the message ? Contains the Corp Label

msg_geolocation.name: msg_geolocation
msg_geolocation.comment: Geo zone considered by the messages. Contains the Corp Label

msg_content_type.name: msg_content_type
msg_content_type.comment: Type of contents that will be in the messages. Contains the Corp Label

msg_secondary_universes.name: msg_secondary_universes
msg_secondary_universes.comment: These are the secondary universes discussed in the message. Multiple values possible. Same picklist values as MSG_MAIN_UNIVERSE. Contains a list of codes seperated by a coma ','.

msg_country_field1.name: msg_country_field1
msg_country_field1.comment: Picklist that will be named and made available by the administrator of the BU. Contains the Corp Label

msg_country_field2.name: msg_country_field2
msg_country_field2.comment: Picklist that will be named and made available by the administrator of the BU Contains the Corp Label

msg_objective.name: msg_objective
msg_objective.comment: Goal of the message associated to this campaign. Multiple values possible. Contains the Corp Label

msg_id.name: msg_id
msg_id.comment: Primary key Technical Id of the message

msg_control_group.name: msg_control_group
msg_control_group.comment: This field contains the name of the Data Extension selected as a control group for this message

msg_franchise.name: msg_franchise
msg_franchise.comment: Selector if it is a franchise. Defatult value = False

msg_main_universe.name: msg_main_universe
msg_main_universe.comment: This is the main universe of the theme discussed in the message
